    "body": "## Summary\n- `configure_deep_gemm_num_sms` crashes with `NameError` when `SGLANG_ENABLE_JIT_DEEPGEMM=0` because `deep_gemm` module is not imported\n- Skip the SM count override when JIT is disabled by checking `ENABLE_JIT_DEEPGEMM` (already defined in the same file)\n- Affects SM120 (Blackwell RTX) where DeepGEMM lacks support, and any platform where users explicitly disable DeepGEMM JIT\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] `SGLANG_ENABLE_JIT_DEEPGEMM=0 python -c \"from sglang.srt.layers.deep_gemm_wrapper.entrypoint import configure_deep_gemm_num_sms; ...\"`  passes without crash\n- [x] Normal path (`SGLANG_ENABLE_JIT_DEEPGEMM=1`) unchanged — deep_gemm SM count override still works\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
